  <title>Gck.Allocator</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function onAllocator(data: void, length: Number(gsize)): void {
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>An allocator used to allocate data for the attributes in this GckAttributes set.</p>  <p>This is a function that acts like g_realloc. Specifically it frees when length is
set to zero, it allocates when data is set to NULL, and it reallocates when both
are valid.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>data</code></title>
  <p>Memory to allocate or deallocate.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>length</code></title>
  <p>New length of memory.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>The allocated memory, or NULL when freeing.</p>
</item>
</terms>

